The Prague Stock Exchange crashes down against closing business.
After the steep waste in the morning, the Prague stock exchange was able to correct the losses.
Transactions with ČEZ’s shares reached almost half of the normal day-to-day business.
The Prague stock exchange was linked to the fall on Monday at the beginning of Tuesday’s trades, as it fell another six percentage points.
This time, the reason for the burglary was Wall Street.
In the Czech Republic, too, the reaction of the market to the result of the vote of the American House of Representatives, which had refused to support a stabilization plan for the financial sector there.
Fall of shares in Asia
A dramatic case experienced on Tuesday on the Asian stock exchanges, although the indices were able to offset part of the losses over the course of the day.
The index of the Hong Kong Hang Seng stock exchange lost nearly four percentage points over the course of the business day, but was later able to compensate for some of the losses, thus decreasing to about 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index, which observed the movement of Chinese stocks on the Hong Kong stock exchange, fell 3.8 percent, while markets in Shanghai were closed.
Shares on the Sydney stock exchange lost more than five percent, but then reduced losses to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan stock market fell by 3.6 percent after the index.
“The timing for the U.S. rescue operation is uncertain and will affect financial markets around the world,” said Joseph Yam, chief of the monetary agency in Hong Kong.
Hong Kong determines, although it belongs to China, its monetary policy itself, i.e. independently of the Chinese central bank.
Interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, the U.S. legislators should return to the negotiating table as soon as possible and approve the draft support for the financial system.
Otherwise, there is a threat that other countries will be affected by the invasion.
A Bloodbath of American Stocks
The U.S. House of Representatives on Monday rejected the plan to support the financial system, for which up to $700 billion (nearly 12 trillion CZK) should be spent.
Legislators thus ignored President George Bush’s call to support the plan.
In Bush’s view, the plan would resolve the fundamental causes of the financial crisis and thus help stabilize the entire economy.
U.S. stocks experienced a bloodshed on Monday, and the main stock indices recorded the biggest decline in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones index fell by nearly seven percent, with a similar drop last seen in 1987.
The index had already fallen before the vote, but there was little evidence that the draft would not pass through in the House of Representatives, the index experienced a free fall.
Congress makes concession: U.S. government can pump $700 billion into banks
The top representatives of the U.S. Congress and the administration of President George W. Bush have agreed on a broader form of agreement on financial assistance to the U.S. financial system.
This will be voted at the beginning of next week.
U.S. legislators reached a breakthrough in talks about the adoption of a rescue plan in the form of a financial aid to the U.S. financial system in the amount of $700 billion (about 12 trillion crowns).
However, this does not mean a victory yet.
Congressmen have to negotiate some details of the agreement before they can publish and vote on the final version of the law.
The plan to support the financial system will be negotiated at the US Congress on Monday.
On Sunday, the chairman of the Committee on Banking and Financial Services Barney Frank told Reuters.
In the Senate, according to different data, the plan could probably be voted at the earliest on Wednesday.
According to economists, a notice that the plan is to be adopted should be the first significant psychological factor for a revival of the financial markets.
Afterwards, however, there is a "disappointment" due to the complicated mechanisms of how to help markets also in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
“We have made significant progress.
We have clarified our different views on what a package to stabilize the market should look like," Democrat Nancy Pelosi told Bloomberg agency.
He said a final vote could be held on Sunday.
Legislators met with U.S. Finance Minister Henry Paulson on Sunday night to give the government fund its final form.
This provides for the purchase of unsold mortgage assets from financial companies, which will plunge financial companies into serious losses and jeopardize the stability of the entire system.
“We are on the verge of a definitive agreement on a plan that will work and must be effective in the market.
We have to continue the healing plan even further, but I think we’re at the target,” Paulson said.
A Signal for Asian Business
The global financial crisis is also clearly reflected in the stock markets, which are declining sharply.
According to Nevada Democratic Senator Harry Reid, legislators are striving to reach a final agreement before Sunday in Congress.
This is to reassure investors from deals on the Asian financial markets, which are in the first time zone, where a Congressional decision could affect business on Monday.
However, it is still not clear when both chambers of the American Congress will vote on the law, and there is also uncertainty as to whether the negotiations at the last minute could fail to address a problem.
Legislators hope it will be adopted in the coming days.
However, the law will undergo some changes.
The total amount destined to assist the system will be divided into two parts.
The initial $350 billion will be made available as soon as possible, as President George Bush called for.
But Congress can block the disbursement of the remaining money if it feels that the program does not fulfill its function, at another $100 billion and later at the final $350 billion.
Bush says progress in negotiations is positive
While the President has a veto right in this decision, Congress can over-vote his veto.
However, despite these changes, the basic idea of the program, which was based on obtaining finances for the purchase of poor mortgage bonds whose value has dropped, has remained because hundreds of thousands of Americans are no longer able to repay their mortgages.
“We’ve worked out everything.
The House of Representatives should be able to vote on the law on Sunday, then the Senate on Monday," said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
President Bush was also satisfied with the progress.
His spokesman, Tony Fratto, said Bush was satisfied with Saturday’s progress and “appreciates the two-sided effort to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy.”
Limitation of golden parachutes
Senate banking committee chairman Christopher Dodd, the senior negotiator, said the legislators agreed on a responsibility for the money program, the protection of taxpayers from losses, the completion of benefits and a timetable for the plan’s financing.
The new law also aims to restrict the so-called golden parachutes for directors of the companies involved in the programme and to set up a committee to oversee the fund.
This is to be directed by the Ministry of Finance.
“We’ve worked very hard on it and made great progress towards a deal that works and is important for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also expects help for homeowners who have problems with repaying their mortgage.
The government should negotiate new rates on mortgages that it buys off, with the goal of lowering the monthly costs for debtors and enabling them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological help
According to Patria Finance chief economist David Marek, the proposed plan is a good idea, but it will be very difficult to implement.
"And that's because we don't know through which mechanism and at what price the problematic assets are bought.
This will be crucial to how the financial sector and the government divide the losses among themselves,” Marek told iHNed.cz this week.
Whether the plan will be adopted now or early next week is not crucial in Marek’s view.
“It’s more important that Congressmen agree to support the plan and approve it as soon as possible.
The psychological significance of the agreement that an adoption is coming is the most important thing at this moment,” Marek said.
