Rather, there are irregularities in speed.
The probes become unexpectedly faster or slower.
So far, physicists have not been able to explain this effect.
They named him swing-by anomaly.
Some experts worry that perhaps even Albert Einstein’s general relativity theory, which describes the attractiveness of matter by curving space, might not be quite correct.
