Space researchers have known about the existence of dark matter only for about ten years.
It obviously comes from an attraction, the effect of which can be observed on other celestial bodies.
It itself, on the other hand, is completely invisible, i.e. it does not transmit and reflect any electromagnetic radiation, especially not visible light.
