Nevertheless, the question to Obama is whether his commitment to bilingual education, which focuses on teaching in languages other than English, contradicts his interest in reducing the distance in school performance.
Take as an example "Sixth Street Prep", a primary school in eastern Los Angeles.
The majority of students are Spanish and come from low-income families.
