Speaking in Sleep
Some children talk at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us what happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Of course, more than one of you was told that you were talking at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (one time in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Relationships are often sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for it.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overload.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that you can speak quietly in single words, whisper, or it can be quite the opposite (crying, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the statement is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult with a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and thus occurs.
We said it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are awful and a bit too wild.
In nervous children who are recommended relaxation, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner rest.
This helps the child to sleep quietly.
When talking happens in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless for the child and the next day it will be unable to remember what happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear it out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, it sleeps, so it rests.
Remember, if you are afraid after a pair of appearances, it is recommended to get advice or find out what reason the child is afraid of.
When they understand what it says (which is not so ordinary), the child does not put pressure to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
