Grapefruit juice was already suspected to be responsible for increasing the effects of some medications such as antibiotics, anti-asthma, cardiovascular medications, anxiolytic and neurological agents, up to toxic levels.
The same drug agency warned doctors and patients about the dangers of this mix two years ago, emphasizing that they should be careful about what they drink in combination with drugs such as diazepan or metadon.
IS NOT ONLY GRAPFRUIT – According to experts, orange juice and apple juice also contain substances that can inhibit the drugs.
The list of active ingredients inhibited by fruit juices is long.
Hence the appeal of Michele Carruba, Director of the Università Statale di Milano: "Such results are usually immediately forwarded to the various international manufacturers, who are thus free to change the consumer information.
