The links between politics and 'Ndrangheta lead to the arrest of the mayor of Gioia Tauro
"The mayor of Gioia Tauro was willing to adapt the decisions of the municipality to the interests of the mafia group Piromalli.
The accusations of the Anti-Mafia Law Office of Calabria against Mayor Giorgio Dal Torrione and his deputy Rosario Schiavone of the municipality of Gioia Tauro, who were arrested this morning for involvement in mafia business, are serious.
In handcuffs, Gioacchino Piromalli, the older mediator between the clan and the public administration, and his nephew: the lawyer, who bears the same name as the boss of the clan, had already been sentenced for involvement in criminal associations of the mafia, at the time to a compensation of 10 million euros.
“In disrespect of every moral and legal standard,” the lawyers write, “the two local administrations had decided to pay the lawyer Piromalli money for consulting activities.”
Thus, it had been made possible for the mafia group – according to the judges – to invade the town halls officially and to co-decide the policy of public administration.
The president of the regional committee of Calabria Agazio Loyero does not deny that in his region "it is anything but an exception to encounter connections of local administrations and organized crime." "There are places where the concentration of the mafia is greater than in others where such connections are practically inevitable.
But there are also local politicians who resist the pressure of the 'Ndrangheta: heroes who preserve a white vest."
The arrests of this morning follow those of last July, according to the police of the Piromalli clan.
Since the end of last April, the municipal council of Gioia Tauro had been dissolved, but as early as 1991 – and also then due to alleged links between organized crime and local administration – local politicians had been expelled from their municipal offices.
Giorgio Dal Torrione, then mayor of the Udc, was elected head of the middle-right coalition after the May 2006 ballot election.
He screamed scandal when the prefecture ordered the dissolution of the municipal council.
He asked Deputy Interior Minister Marco Minniti, whom he accused of having invented everything for political and strategic reasons, but the judges declare in connection with this morning’s arrest warrant that the Piromalli clan had even dared to ask for an amendment to the A3 project.
